: false, "is_admin": false, "score": 34, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "apu", "id": 8629596, "raw_content": "Thomas Massie's largest campaign donor is Jeff Yass, an American Jewish billionaire, according to a May 20, 2026 post cited in ZeroHedge.  \r\n\r\nYass is described as a key figure in the Kohelet Policy Forum, a far-right Israeli think tank, and a major contributor to Massie\u2019s campaign\r\n\r\nKohelet Policy Forum Funding: Yass, along with co-founder Arthur Dantchik, has been reported to provide significant financial support to Kohelet, which helped draft Israel\u2019s Nation-State Law and the controversial 2023 judicial reforms. \r\n\r\nPolicy Goals: Kohelet\u2019s stated aims include securing Israel\u2019s future as the nation-state of the Jewish people, promoting free-market principles, and influencing U.S. policy to shield Israel from criticism.\r\n\r\nIn other words, it was essentially two sides of AIPAC type funding playing both sides, and the pro Massie side somehow overlooked this completely, ans got duped by an something so public and obvious. \r\n\r\n", "author": "MagaJay02", "created": 1779282579210, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "MagaJay02", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Those claiming Massie was about Jewsish interest VS American interest, Massies top donor is Jewish, & part of the \"Greater Israel Project\" \ud83d\ude06 ", "last_comment_created": 1779289506800, "content": "<p>Thomas Massie's largest campaign donor is Jeff Yass, an American Jewish billionaire, according to a May 20, 2026 post cited in ZeroHedge.</p>\n<p>Yass is described as a key figure in the Kohelet Policy Forum, a far-right Israeli think tank, and a major contributor to Massie\u2019s campaign</p>\n<p>Kohelet Policy Forum Funding: Yass, along with co-founder Arthur Dantchik, has been reported to provide significant financial support to Kohelet, which helped draft Israel\u2019s Nation-State Law and the controversial 2023 judicial reforms.</p>\n<p>Policy Goals: Kohelet\u2019s stated aims include securing Israel\u2019s future as the nation-state of the Jewish people, promoting free-market principles, and influencing U.S. policy to shield Israel from criticism.</p>\n<p>In other words, it was essentially two sides of AIPAC type funding playing both sides, and the pro Massie side somehow overlooked this completely, ans got duped by an something so public and obvious.</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 19, "score_up": 34, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "BE\u00a0\u00a0LESS\u00a0\u00a0RETARDED", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "2057112317150499320", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASsZ5tCDa", "is_twitter": true, "is_admin": false, "score": 18, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8630022, "raw_content": "", "author": "blockchain-the-vote", "created": 1779295009375, "profile_picture": "qNV5Yu864PFJ", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "blockchain-the-vote", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "twitter.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASsZ5tCDa.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://twitter.com/visegrad24/status/2057112317150499320", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Yeah I'm thinking it's not just a political movement", "last_comment_created": 177